If that is a problem: you could create a generic proxy with your own `InvocationHandler` - this is exactly what `AnnotationParser` is doing for you internally. Or you use your own implementation of `MyAnnotation` as defined [here](/questions/16299717/how-to-create-an-instance-of-an-annotation#16303007). In both cases you should remember to implement `annotationType()`, `equals()` and `hashCode()` as the result is documented specifically for `java.lang.Annotation`.

The proxy approach, as suggested in [Gunnar&#39;s answer][1] is already implemented in [GeantyRef][2]:

    Map&lt;String, Object&gt; annotationParameters = new HashMap&lt;&gt;();
