Annotation instances produced this way will act identical to the ones produced by Java normally, and their `hashCode` and `equals` have been implemented properly for compatibility, so no bizarre caveats like with directly instantiating the annotation as in the accepted answer. In fact, JDK internally uses this same approach: [sun.reflect.annotation.AnnotationParser#annotationForMap][3].

